Error handling and validation---
alwaysApply: true
---
- Always check for null/undefined before accessing properties
- Validate room exists before processing
- Check creep exists and is not null before operations
- Use Log.error() for critical errors
- Use Log.warn() for warnings
- Use Log.debug() for Development/debugging information (e.g., detailed state, intermediate values)
- Use Log.info() for Important operational events (e.g., successful actions, state changes)
- Use Log.success() for Successful completion of important operations
- Use Log.test() for Test messages for development/debugging (always displayed, bypasses level checks)
- Handle structure destruction gracefully
- Validate structure type before casting
